The action icons displayed at the top of the XML Writer's configuration page allow to perform global actions on the XML data structure.

**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Import**](/doxee-platform/docs/4-dt3-xml-writer-global-actions#importing-a-data-schema)

Define the structure to write XML output files by importing an existing structure, schema, XML or XSD file.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Download structure**

Download a copy of the data structure to your local filesystem in XML format (for example: *Writer_structure.xml*).

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

[**Settings**](/doxee-platform/docs/4-dt3-xml-writer-global-actions#configuring-the-xml-writers-general-settings)

Define the general settings of the XML Writer's output XML file.

### Importing a data schema
This feature allows to define the structure to write XML input files using a previously exported Data Transformation schema or structure, or an external XML or XSD file.

The functionality is useful, for example, if you want to import the structure of an existing XML file instead of manually defining the required elements and attributes.

> Note

It is always possible to modify the imported data structure.

> Warning

This action will permanently delete and overwrite the existing data structure.

- Open the XML Writer resource in the configuration editor as described in [Configuring DT3 Project Resources.](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources)

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Import structure**). The system notifies you that uploading a structure file will discard the existing structure.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Click **Yes, continue **to proceed.

- Select the required XML or XSD file to upload using the file browser. The new data structure is automatically loaded into the XML Writer's configuration, overwriting the existing data structure.

### Configuring the XML Writer's general settings
This feature allows to define the writer settings for the fields in the data structure, such as elements and attributes, and other general writer settings for the output XML file, such as for example indentation settings and line separators.

> Note

The system applies the writer settings to all elements and attributes that do not have custom writing settings.

- Open the XML Writer resource in the configuration editor as described in Configuring DT3 Project Resources.

- â€‹Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Settings**). The **Settings **panel is displayed on the right; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Configure the required parameters:

**Section**

**Parameter**

**Description**

**General**

**Name**

Name of the XML Writer

**Description**

*(optional) *Brief description of the XML Writer

**Structure**

**Indent character**

Select the indentation character to use from the drop-down menu. The available options are:

**tab**

- **no space **

- **single space **

- **double space**

**Scope**

Enter a description to define the scope of the output XML file.

> Note

The system reports the description of the scope in the processing completion final report.

**Add XML declaration**

Select this option to add, at the beginning of the output XML file, the declaration of the XML version and encoding used.

> Note

The **Add XML declaration **checkbox is selected by default because the system, by default, adds the declaration of the XML version and encoding used at the beginning of the output XML file.

**Preserve namespace**

Select this option to preserve the namespaces in the imported XML file.

**Schema**

**Schema name**

View and edit the name of the current data schema.

**Manage schemas**

Click on this link to manage the available data schema, as described in [Managing data schemas](/doxee-platform/docs/4-dt3-xml-writer-global-actions#managing-data-schemas) below.

> Tip

The **Applied to **section lists the Data Transformation components using this data schema, allowing you to evaluate the impacts of adding, deleting or modifying its elements.

#### Managing data schemas
- Click on the **Manage schemas **link to open the dedicated panel; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Move your mouse over the name of a data schema to display the context actions; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select one of the available actions:

**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Download**

Download the data schema to your local filesystem.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Rename**

Edit the name of the data schema.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Delete**

Permanently remove the data schema from the project.

> Warning

This action cannot be undone.

If a data schema is currently used by one or more project components, this action is not available.

- If a data schema is used by one or more project components, a blue dot is displayed next to it. Click on it to see which resources are using the structure; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)A detail panel listing the resources already using the selected structure is displayed; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Tip

Click on the name of a resource to open it in its dedicated editor.

It is also possible to download or rename the data schema from this panel.
